---
// Fig 3 — the substrate trade-off axis. Three points, big text.
const { num = '3' } = Astro.props;
---
<figure class="fig">
  <svg viewBox="0 0 720 190" role="img" aria-label="Axis diagram: textual memory sits at the auditable and portable end, parametric memory at the token-cheap but opaque end, latent memory in between.">
    <defs>
      <marker id="f3a" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="8" markerHeight="8" orient="auto-start-reverse">
        <path d="M 0 1 L 9 5 L 0 9 z" fill="var(--muted)"></path>
      </marker>
    </defs>

    <line x1="70" y1="110" x2="650" y2="110" stroke="var(--muted)" stroke-width="2" marker-start="url(#f3a)" marker-end="url(#f3a)"></line>

    <text x="60" y="42" font-size="16" font-weight="600" fill="var(--ink)">auditable, editable,</text>
    <text x="60" y="64" font-size="16" font-weight="600" fill="var(--ink)">survives a model swap</text>
    <text x="660" y="42" text-anchor="end" font-size="16" font-weight="600" fill="var(--ink)">token-cheap,</text>
    <text x="660" y="64" text-anchor="end" font-size="16" font-weight="600" fill="var(--ink)">opaque, model-locked</text>

    <circle cx="140" cy="110" r="9" fill="var(--ink)"></circle>
    <text x="140" y="148" text-anchor="middle" font-size="18" font-weight="600" fill="var(--ink)">textual</text>

    <circle cx="390" cy="110" r="9" fill="none" stroke="var(--ink)" stroke-width="2.5"></circle>
    <text x="390" y="148" text-anchor="middle" font-size="18" font-weight="600" fill="var(--ink)">latent</text>

    <circle cx="610" cy="110" r="9" fill="none" stroke="var(--ink)" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-dasharray="4 3"></circle>
    <text x="610" y="148" text-anchor="middle" font-size="18" font-weight="600" fill="var(--ink)">parametric</text>

    <text x="360" y="182" text-anchor="middle" font-size="14" fill="var(--muted)">every memory system is a point on this line, whether it says so or not</text>
  </svg>
  <figcaption><strong>Fig. {num}.</strong> The substrate trade-off. Text (Mem0, Zep, MemGPT) costs tokens but can be inspected, corrected and carried between models; weights (MemoryLLM, Titans) are cheap to read but impossible to audit; latent states (MemoRAG) sit in between. Production systems cluster at the textual end, and that is not an accident.</figcaption>
</figure>
